President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring March 2, 2016, as Read Across America Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of reading in our lives and the impact it has on children. It also pays tribute to Dr. Seuss and his contributions to children's literature. The proclamation highlights the launch of Open eBooks, a project aimed at providing reading material to underserved communities. It calls upon children, families, educators, and the public to observe the day with appropriate programs and activities.